data.description: Paradise without a passport! Tropical Island living awaits on Snead Island where the Manatee River and Terra Ceia Bay meet at the Gulf. This one-owner, custom built “ Coastal Living” style home is perfectly nestled on a cul-de-sac lot with a saltwater canal leading out to the bay. Eye catching upgrades and picture perfect curb appeal dazzle with a paver driveway, metal roof, lush landscaping and a welcoming front porch. Once inside you’ll find the coastal vibe continue, with a great room layout ready for entertaining large or intimate gatherings. Vaulted ceilings, large windows and glass doors bring natural light and the outdoors in. Large kitchen with plenty of cabinets and surface area with a breakfast bar area connect with the living area. The dining room, with dry bar enjoys a view of the lagoon with jumping fish and seabirds. Designed for Al Fresco entertaining in any climate is the screened rear porch and the open TREX wraparound deck add incredible space for grilling, sunbathing and large gatherings. Your private dock with electric, water and a 12k pound lift is just 3 homes from open water. Back inside there are three large bedrooms, each with en-suite, wood floors, a power room for guests and a laundry room with sink and additional closet storage. Have hobbies? The 3 car garage with workshop includes a handy rear door for easy access of boating or camping gear. Upgraded impact windows and doors, sprinkler system, extensive outdoor lighting and more awaits. Unique "Key West style" charm abounds the community of Snead Island in Palmetto, where the casual laid-back lifestyle is the envy of the Gulf Coast. Heritage Bay, a special enclave of island inspired homes offers it's lucky residents a private pool and tennis court. Bounded by the Manatee River, Tampa Bay and Terra Ceia Bay, Snead Island is a nature lover's paradise and features events like an annual 5K trail run, community Fish Fry, Christmas golf cart parade and a luminaries night. Convenient to community amenities, and situated near the Bradenton Yacht Club, Emerson Preserve Park, plus an easy commute to St. Pete and Tampa and Sarasota. *Transferable Flood Insurance Policy for $1,033 Per Year*
